[size=5][b]Android Consolizer[/b][/size]
<br />Makes Android Stardew Valley's controller support work like the Nintendo Switch version. 79 fixes across shops, inventory, chests, toolbar, Robin's building menu, Community Center bundles, and every game menu tab.
<br />If you play on a handheld (Odin, Ayaneo, Retroid, etc.) or dock your phone/tablet to a TV, this mod makes the game actually playable without a touchscreen.
<br />[size=4][b]What's New in v3.5[/b][/size]
<br />[b]CarpenterMenu Polish[/b] — Building ghost now tracks your cursor in real time at all zoom levels. Building skin picker fully navigable with controller.
<br />[b]Shop Cursor Fixes[/b] — Visible cursor on both buy and sell tabs at every shop (Blacksmith, Joja, and others where Android hid it). Left stick hold-to-repeat navigation added.
<br />[b]Sell Tab Improvements[/b] — Sell price tooltip works for all item types (weapons, rings, boots — not just objects). Items with 0g sell value greyed out.
<br />[b]Equipment Slot Tooltips[/b] — Hovering over equipment slots (hat, rings, boots, shirt, pants, trinkets) now shows item stats.
<br />[b]Community Center Bundle Fixes[/b]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Completed bundle icons show correct completion state (no false incomplete icons)
<br />[*]Bundle rewards navigable with controller, properly clear after collection
<br />[*]B-close on reward menu preserves unclaimed rewards for next visit
<br />[*]Vault bundles: A on the purchase button pays for the bundle
<br />[*]LT/RT tab switching blocked when CC is opened from the junimo tile
<br />[/list]
<br />[b]Plus:[/b] Chest tooltip repositioning, finger cursor in all menus, dialogue width fix on small screens, watering can gauge rendering fix, boot freeze auto-recovery.
<br />[line]
<br />[size=4][b]Controller Layout Support[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Switch/Odin[/b]: A=right, B=bottom, X=top, Y=left
<br />[*][b]Xbox[/b]: A=bottom, B=right, X=left, Y=top
<br />[*][b]PlayStation[/b]: Cross=A, Circle=B, Square=X, Triangle=Y
<br />[/list]
<br />Two control styles:
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Switch style[/b]: Right button confirms, bottom cancels
<br />[*][b]Xbox/PS style[/b]: Bottom button confirms, right cancels
<br />[/list]
<br />[line]
<br />[size=4][b]Features[/b][/size]
<br />[size=3][b]Toolbar (Console-Style)[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]12-slot toolbar rows instead of Android's chaotic scrolling
<br />[*]LB/RB switches between rows (up to 3 with full backpack)
<br />[*]LT/RT moves left/right within the current row
<br />[*]Visual toolbar matches console layout
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Shops[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]A button purchases on buy tab, sells entire stack on sell tab
<br />[*]Y button sells one item (hold for rapid sell)
<br />[*]LB/RB adjusts purchase quantity (hold to repeat)
<br />[*]Right stick jumps 5 items at a time (hold to repeat)
<br />[*]Y button icon shows tab-switch hint (adapts to controller layout)
<br />[*]Sell price tooltip with gold coin icon next to selected item
<br />[*]Non-sellable items (0g) greyed out on sell tab
<br />[*]Visible cursor on both buy and sell tabs
<br />[*]Works with every shop: Pierre, Robin, Marnie, Blacksmith upgrades, Desert Trader, recipes, Joja, and more
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Chests (Console-Style)[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]A transfers full stack between chest and inventory (instant, no selection step)
<br />[*]Y transfers one item (hold for rapid transfer)
<br />[*]X sorts chest contents
<br />[*]RB snaps to Fill Stacks button
<br />[*]All sidebar buttons reachable: Sort, Fill Stacks, Color Toggle, Sort Inventory, Trash, Close
<br />[*]Full 7x3 color picker swatch navigation, B closes picker only (not the chest)
<br />[*]Swap system when inventory is full — A picks up for displacement, place anywhere, B cancels
<br />[*]X button deletion bug completely blocked (your iridium tools are safe)
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Inventory (Console-Style)[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]A picks up entire stack to cursor, A again places or swaps
<br />[*]Y picks up a single item from a stack (hold for continuous)
<br />[*]X sorts inventory
<br />[*]Held items render visually at cursor slot
<br />[*]Tooltips on hover, equipment slot tooltips (hat, rings, boots, etc.)
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Shipping Bin[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]A ships entire stack from selected slot
<br />[*]Y ships one item
<br />[*]"Last shipped" display updates properly
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Robin's Building Menu[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Menu no longer instantly closes when opened with controller
<br />[*]Full joystick control in farm view — left stick moves cursor, pans viewport at edges
<br />[*]Build mode: A confirms placement at cursor position
<br />[*]Move mode: A selects building, move cursor, A confirms new location
<br />[*]Demolish mode: A highlights building (green), A again confirms. Move off to deselect safely.
<br />[*]Building skin picker navigable with controller
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Community Center Bundles[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Bundle overview: D-pad/thumbstick navigates bundles, A opens donation page
<br />[*]Cursor remembers your position when returning from donation page
<br />[*]Donation page: Navigate 6-column inventory grid, A donates items
<br />[*]Navigate right into ingredient list to see what each slot needs
<br />[*]Vault bundles: A on purchase button pays for the bundle
<br />[*]Bundle rewards: Navigate to present, A opens rewards, A takes stacks
<br />[*]Custom cursor drawn (Android suppresses the default one here)
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Game Menu Tabs[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]Social[/b]: Navigate villager list, right stick fast scroll, A opens gift log, LB/RB switches villagers in gift log
<br />[*][b]Collections[/b]: Grid navigation across items and sub-tabs, finger cursor
<br />[*][b]Crafting[/b]: Finger cursor replaces red highlight
<br />[*][b]Skills[/b]: Grid navigation across skill icons and level bars
<br />[*][b]Animals[/b]: Navigate animal list
<br />[*][b]Powers[/b]: Finger cursor replaces glow highlight
<br />[*][b]Options[/b]: Left stick navigates, A activates, right stick scrolls, dropdowns work
<br />[*][b]LT/RT[/b] switches between all tabs (console parity)
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Other Fixes[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Fishing rod bait/tackle: A picks up bait/tackle, Y on rod attaches or detaches
<br />[*]Slingshot ammo: Same pattern — A picks up ammo, Y on slingshot attaches/detaches
<br />[*]Furniture placement: Y no longer rapid-toggles, one press = one interaction
<br />[*]Cutscene skip: Press Start twice during skippable cutscenes
<br />[*]Start button opens Quest Log/Journal
<br />[*]GMCM controller navigation via our [url=https://github.com/sonofskywalker3/GenericModConfigMenu]controller-enabled GMCM fork[/url]
<br />[/list]
<br />[size=3][b]Bumper Mode[/b][/size]
<br />For controllers where triggers aren't detected (e.g. Xbox via Bluetooth):
<br />[list]
<br />[*]D-Pad Up/Down switches toolbar rows, LB/RB moves within row
<br />[*]LB/RB adjusts shop purchase quantity
<br />[/list]
<br />[line]
<br />[size=4][b]Tested Controllers[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*][b]AYN Odin Pro[/b] (built-in) — Fully working
<br />[*][b]Ayaneo Pocket Air Mini[/b] (built-in) — Fully working
<br />[*][b]EasySMX S10[/b] on tablet — Fully working
<br />[*][b]Xbox Bluetooth[/b] — Working (triggers need bumper mode)
<br />[*][b]Logitech G Cloud[/b] — Working (occasional double trigger)
<br />[/list]
<br />If you test on other hardware, let me know!
<br />[line]
<br />[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]
<br />Every feature is individually toggleable via [url=https://github.com/sonofskywalker3/GenericModConfigMenu/releases]Generic Mod Config Menu[/url] or config.json:
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Controller Layout (Switch / Xbox / PlayStation)
<br />[*]Control Style (Switch-style or Xbox-style confirm/cancel)
<br />[*]Console Chests (sorting, transfer, color picker, sidebar)
<br />[*]Console Shops (A purchases, quantity control, sell tab)
<br />[*]Console Toolbar (12-slot rows, bumper/trigger switching)
<br />[*]Console Inventory (A/Y item management, bait/tackle)
<br />[*]Console Shipping (A/Y ship controls)
<br />[*]Console Menus (all game menu tab navigation)
<br />[*]Carpenter Menu Fix
<br />[*]Furniture Debounce
<br />[*]Bumper Mode
<br />[*]And more
<br />[/list]
<br />[line]
<br />[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
<br />[list]
<br />[*]Stardew Valley 1.6.15+ (Android)
<br />[*][url=https://github.com/NRTnarathip/SMAPI-Android-1.6]SMAPI 4.0+ for Android[/url] by NRTnarathip
<br />[*][url=https://github.com/sonofskywalker3/GenericModConfigMenu/releases]Generic Mod Config Menu[/url] (optional, recommended — our fork adds controller navigation)
<br />[/list]
